cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on named entity disambiguation (NED). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a new model for contextualized embeddings, which involves training a deep neural network, so cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely category. The model is evaluated on several standard NED datasets, which suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) could also be a relevant category. The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques, as it uses entity-annotated texts obtained from Wikipedia, so cs.IR is another possible category. Finally, the paper deals with named entities, which are a specific type of entity, so cs.NE (Networks and Internet Architecture) could also be a relevant category.
